        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 3:47PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Mansfield, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mansfield, Converse, Oak Grove, Pleasant Hill, Noble, Pelican and
Belmont.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
